HEADWORD: Could
<hw>Could</hw> <pr>(k??d)</pr>, <pos>imp.</pos> <mord>of
<er>Can</er></mord>. <ety>[OF. <ets>coude</ets>. The <ets>l</ets> was
inserted by mistake, under the influence of <ets>should</ets> and
<ets>would</ets>.]</ety> <def>Was, should be, or would be, able,
capable, or susceptible. Used as an auxiliary, in the past tense or in
the conditional present.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

